    "client_msg_id": "9695ba65-d040-421c-a40e-2b8c760f05d8",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I've read Jef Raskin's _The Humane Interface_ and other writings against modes. I generally find them persuasive (even as a vi-keybinding-user). But I still see mode problems _everywhere_ in UIs, and see people stumble with them. The most common is focus — I _think_ focus is on one element or in one window, when it is actually elsewhere, so my input goes to the wrong place. Have \"we\" generally decided that mode errors aren't as much of a problem after all?",
    "user": "U04E5QAD6DD",
