    "client_msg_id": "3b016bfb-5f22-4fc1-be60-1537e417b05a",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "&gt;  That would mean everything the computer does MUST follow same Interface Guidelines™, which I agree is nice for users, but also implies program authors can't experiment with unusual interfaces.\nThis is more-or-less what made me accept (and still sometimes hate) the web as a platform. There are no (all that useful) UI standards, but there is a *ton* of room for UI innovation.\n\nHard to tell if it is worth the usability cost, or how much we ought to be making user interface experiments on unwitting users.",
    "user": "U04E5QAD6DD",
    "ts": "1700575720.942189",
    "blocks": [
